    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-05-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-05-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="855"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d855">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to Ambassador <persName
                            type="to">Meyer</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-05-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 1, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 18.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose copy of a note from the Japanese
                    minister at this capital, who, under the instructions of his government,
                    requests the use of your good offices to obtain the release and exchange of
                    certain noncombatant prisoners mentioned in the list annexed to the note.<note
                        n="b" xml:id="d855fnb">Printed under Japan, <ref target="#pg_601">p.
                            601</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>You will at once bring the matter to the attention of the Imperial
                    Government.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
